# Hook driving detection — label rewrite is forbidden

## Goal

Unlock the **native** Maps projected keyboard (`rek.d` / `reh.b` / `snp.j`+`k`) by **spoofing driving and keyboard-restriction detection** in Maps and gearhead.

## Out of scope — do not implement

**Search bar hint / label rewrite must not be added, restored, or used as fallback.**

Forbidden:

- `Resources.getString` / `getText` hint substitution
- `VoicePlateHints`, `CarText` / placeholder rewriting
- Rewriting `qha.hintString` or `kur.aJ` return values in afterHook
- `MAPS-HINT-001`, `GH-HINT-001`, or similar string-patch layers

“Voice only while driving” means **driving hooks failed** — fix `kur.aJ`, `qha`, `trt.i()`, `qwt`, `csrh`, `qhf.l`. Do not hide the label.

Read [docs/DESIGN_GOALS.md](../docs/DESIGN_GOALS.md).
